{% extends 'Front/layout.html.twig' %}

{% block container %}
    {{ parent() }}

    <div class="row">
        <div class="page-header">
            <h1>PuPHPet</h1>
        </div>

        <div class="span6">
            <h3>What is this?</h3>

            <p>
                PuPHPet is for rapid generation of Vagrant VMs provisioned by Puppet, specifically made for those that
                don't have the time or interest in learning the details.
            </p>

            <p>
                The idea came to me when I was struggling to get from no previous Vagrant/Puppet knowledge to simply
                having a running VM I could start developing on. Why should I need to learn the ins and outs when
                all I want to do is faceroll more code?
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="span6">
            <h3>Who is it for?</h3>

            <p>
                This is aimed at PHP developers that do not have the time or inclination to learn a whole new system.
                You want to get started programming on an easily managed VM quickly, with as little fuss as possible.
            </p>

            <p>
                This is not meant to be used in production. The choices are limited by design, I will probably only
                ever focus on the official Vagrant Ubuntu boxes, and as of right now you cannot choose specific
                versions of packages to install, only the latest of each.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="page-header">
            <h1>Get Started!</h1>
        </div>

        <form class="form-horizontal" action="/create" method="post" enctype="application/x-www-form-urlencoded">
            <div class="row">{% include 'Front/Tabs/vagrantBox.html.twig' %}</div>
            <div class="clearfix"></div>
            <div id="serverBasics">{% include 'Front/Tabs/server.html.twig' %}</div>
            <div class="clearfix"></div>

            <h2 class="page-header">Web server</h2>
            <div class="webserver-configuration tabbable"> <!-- Only required for left/right tabs -->
                <ul class="nav nav-tabs">
                    <li class="active"><a href="#webserver-apache" data-toggle="tab" rel="apache">Apache</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#webserver-nginx" data-toggle="tab" rel="nginx">nginx</a></li>
                </ul>
                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="webserver-apache">
                        <div id="apache">{% include 'Front/Tabs/apache.html.twig' %}</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="webserver-nginx">
                        <div id="nginx">{% include 'Front/Tabs/nginx.html.twig' %}</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="clearfix"></div>


            <div id="php">{% include 'Front/Tabs/php.html.twig' %}</div>
            <div class="clearfix"></div>
            <div id="mysql">{% include 'Front/Tabs/mysql.html.twig' %}</div>
            <div class="clearfix"></div>
            <div id="create">{% include 'Front/Tabs/create.html.twig' %}</div>

            <input type="hidden" name="webserver" value="apache" />
        </form>
    </div>
{% endblock %}
